\section*{The Quiet Joy of Photography}
\addcontentsline{toc}{section}{The Quiet Joy of Photography}
\begin{multicols}{2}
\noindent Pablo Picasso the celebrated artist once said "the meaning of life is to find your gift, the purpose of life is to give it away."Radhakrishna Pai in this repertoire of pictures, makes an effort to capture this very spirit !There is a special kind of magic that happens when the photographer does not chase the moment but waits for it. His photography invites you to slow down breathe and truly see Nature as it exists. In the wild flora and fauna share a heartbeat. Coexistence exists. His pictures are worth a thousand words. The stunning close ups to breath taking wild life moments !! These compelling pictures celebrate his journey of bird watching. "We often do not encounter rare species, so his repertoire of pics are the 1st step in acknowledging their value and the need for protecting Mother nature"

Think of this book as a story telling endeavour that celebrates a relationship between people and birds and the ecosystem that is the very sustenance of life on this earth.

"May he continue to enrich our knowledge on birds.. Angels of the sky".

“!Enjoy.........

\end{multicols}
\attribution{Arundhati Dhareshwar\\"Parijata" Vittal}
\newpage

\section*{Dva Suparna…}
\addcontentsline{toc}{section}{Dva Suparna…}
\begin{multicols}{2}
\noindent This itself is Tapas (austerity). There is no doubt about it. Patience, faith, precision, understanding, endurance of hardship, and deep concentration when all these are refined and matured, that itself becomes Tapas. It is a meditative state of being.

For the sake of a single photograph, the mind remains silently absorbed in meditation, always praying that the bird searching for its nest may have its wings strengthened until it reaches its goal. Those who understand say that a photographer becomes what he meditates upon. Creation is an act of joy performed in a semi-awakened state, and neither the detail nor the destiny of creation is known to anyone in advance.

Just as the bird, in a meditative state, patiently waits for its goal, the one who photographs it also waits, becoming a beautiful part of that very bird's journey. When the bird achieves its goal, the joy it experiences is the same joy the photographer feels after capturing the image.

It gives us great happiness to write these words about my dear friend Radhakrishna Pai. Along with the many photographs he has already published, he has spent countless meaningful moments for many more unpublished images that still reside within him. In this commercial world, possessing such a contemplative and sensitive mind is no small thing.

From the depths of my heart, I extend my best wishes to this work being published, and to its creator my young friend Radhakrishna Pai.

\end{multicols}
\attribution{— M. Ananthakrishna Hebbar\\"Saaranga", Vittla}
\newpage

\section*{Pai’s This Venture Has Re-Ignited My Love for Life}
\addcontentsline{toc}{section}{Pai’s This Venture Has Re-Ignited My Love for Life}
\begin{multicols}{2}
\noindent Many years back when I was going to Late Janardhan Pai's shop for my home needs, I was observing his teenaged son Radhakrishna Pai. Later both me and R. K. Pai joined JCI of Vittal and were attending regular meetings. Then one after another both of us were elected as presidents of Vittal chapter of the organization and our chapter hosted conferences in our town during both of our periods! Both of us were the members of Vittal Jaycees Education Society, Vittal and later became Secretary and directors respectively and we become close.

His father Late Janardhana Pai started business and established many industries in Vittal. He was a philanthropist and was in education and religious fields apart from showing interest in literature. Radhakrishna Pai expanded and diversified his father's business and industry and gave employment to many youths. He showed his interest in photography especially of birds! He continued his work in education and religious fields as well. Mr. Pai's photography was not only in many places of our state and other Indian states but also abroad including Africa.

Because of my old age, I slowly withdrew myself from Jaycee Training, Jaycee School, book publication and grammar teaching in various schools. Hence I was away from almost all social activities. One fine day Mr. Pai gave me his writings about his photographic experience to read. Suddenly, after reading them my mood changed and I started to love and live life once again. Such was his enthusiasm, commitment and dedication in bird photography. His writings exhibited his love for birds and his respect for mother nature! I hope this book reaches many people and wish his bird photography and his business a bright future.

\end{multicols}
\newpage
\begin{multicols}{2}
\noindent From the depths of my heart, I extend my best wishes to this work being published, and to its creator my young friend Radhakrishna Pai.

\end{multicols}
\attribution{Shridhar Kodakkal\\Author and Publisher of Educational Books and\\Senior Trainer of JCI – India.}
\newpage

\section*{Nature Through the Judge’s Eyes}
\addcontentsline{toc}{section}{Nature Through the Judge’s Eyes}
\begin{multicols}{2}
\noindent It gives me great pleasure to convey my best wishes for your bird photography journey and this book. Though I am a Judge by profession, my roots are deeply connected to our hometown and my ancestral home near the western coast and the Kelanje Māle forest. My childhood memories amidst nature have nurtured a lifelong bond with forests and wildlife.

Those early experiences with nature give me a special perspective to appreciate and encourage your dedication to bird photography. Through your lens, birds find a voice and nature finds renewed meaning. May this book inspire many to observe, respect, and protect the natural world.

With warm wishes for your continued journey in photography and the conservation of nature.

\end{multicols}
\attribphoto{width=3cm}{judge.jpeg}{— Jayaprakash V.\\Senior Civil Judge \& Judicial Magistrate First Class, Sakleshpura.}
\newpage

